<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Creating a new Site</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Choosing the catalog style</p>
<p class="text">To edit the catalog style, open the site you want
to edit and select Site &gt; Settings and click on the &quot;Page Text&quot; tab.</p>
<p class="text">The catalog style options are:</p>
<ul>
  <li class="text"><strong>Icon view</strong> &#8212; to use this view, select the small icon  to display
    for each item in Item Properties  for each item</li>
  <li class="text"><strong>List view</strong> &#8212; selecting this view simply shows a list of the
    items on the catalog page.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</body>
</html>
